ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How many romantic relationships have you had in the past two years?

Notes: 0= Current Relationship; 1= First Most Recent Relationship; 2= Second Most Recent Relationship; 3= Third Most Recent Relationship; 4= Fourth Most Recent Relationship; 5= Fifth Most Recent Relationship
1= Married; 2= Living together; 3= Dating only each other; 4= Dating each other and other people

ElementDescription: How much do/did you like or love this person?
Notes: 1= Like this person; 2= Really like this person; 3= Love this person; 4= Really love this person; 5= Completely in love with this person

ElementDescription: How much conflict is/was there in the relationship?
Notes: 1= No conflict; 2= Some conflict; 3= Moderate; 4= A lot of conflict; 5= Severe conflict

ElementDescription: If not your current relationship, how did the relationship end?
Notes: 1= I ended it.; 2= Other person ended it.; 3= Mutual decision.; 9= Not applicable, ongoing relationship.

ElementDescription: How distressed were you when the relationship ended?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= Somewhat; 3= Moderate; 4= Very; 5= Extremely
